<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls on World Community to Back Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 20 (Xinhua) -- China, who has always
backed the peace process in Sierra Leone, Friday called upon the
international community to give full support to the implementation
of the peace accord, signed on July 7 in Togo's capital of Lome,
and help the Sierra Leonean people for the early achievement of
the national reconciliation and the economic reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
The statement came as Chen Xu, representative of the Chinese
Mission to the United Nations, took the floor on the draft
resolution on Sierra Leone. Later, the 15-nation Security Council
unanimously adopted the resolution for a provisional expansion of
the U.N. Observer Mission in Sierra Leone (UNOMSIL) up to 210
military observers.
</P>
<P>
"China has always supported the elected government in Sierra
Leone, and supported the peace process in the country," Chen
said.
</P>
<P>
"We have, through various channels, provided various kinds of
assistance to the Sierra Leonean Government and to the West
African Military Observer Group (ECOMOG)," he said. "We will
continue to provide to that country various assistance within our
capabilities."
</P>
<P>
"The peace in Sierra Leone is just beginning, and everything
has to start from scratch, it needs urgent assistance," he said.
"We, at the same time, should see very clearly that peace at
present is very fragile in Sierra Leone, and there are many
uncertain factors in that country."
</P>
<P>
Therefore, "We call upon the international community on the
basis of the forward-looking principle to support the efforts to
carry out the peace agreement and help the Sierra Leonean people
to realize their national reconciliation and begin their economic
reconstruction at an early date," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Government of Sierra Leone and the Revolutionary United
Front signed the peace accord on July 7 in Lome, putting an end to
the eight-year civil war in the West African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
