<HEADLINE> Ugandan President to Address MPs Over Kisangani </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni is to address Parliament about the recent fighting
between Ugandan and Rwandan troops in the Democratic Republic of
Congo.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Apolo Nsibambi had communicated the House
request to the president, the New Vision newspaper said Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, the State House has not yet responded to the request,
the report added.
</P>
<P>
First Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs
Eriya Kategaya Wednesday declined to answer defense related
questions, saying that the president would do so at an appropriate
time.
</P>
<P>
MPs had questioned the rationale of Ugandan troops' prolonged
stay in the Congo following the recent street to street battles
between Ugandan and Rwandan troops in Kisangani.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here observed that the conflict, which claimed dozens
of lives on either side, was the latest twist of event which
further complicated the peace process of the Congo.
</P>
<P>
The fighting began Saturday and lasted to Tuesday. Following
the clashes between the two sides, Ugandan and Rwandan leaders met
in western Uganda and hammered out a cease-fire after two days'
talks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
