<HEADLINE> Tanzania Plans to Sell Two Old Boeings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has agreed in
principle to sell or lease two rather old Boeing 757-200 series
aircraft at the request of Air Tanzania Corporation (ATC).
</P>
<P>
ATC's Public Relations Manager Innocent Mungi said here Friday
that the Ministry of Transport and Communication is in the process
of preparing a paper on the sale or lease of the two aircraft. The
paper will then be presented before the cabinet for decision.
</P>
<P>
Mungi said that the 23-year-old two Boeings are among the
planes categorized as environmentally unfriendly because of the
noises made by the engines, adding that it is quite expensive to
upgrade the engines to a level in compliance with internal
regulations.
</P>
<P>
He said it is a good opportunity at present for the corporation
to dispose the aircraft because they have been evaluated to be
worth between five and six million U.S. dollars each.
</P>
<P>
"The same aircraft will be rated as zero value in the next two
to three years," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
