<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Lebanese Military Tribunal sentenced Thursday two
defendants to two years in prison, one to 18 months, 12 to one
year and eight to six months, contradicting indictments that
requested at least a seven-year sentence for all defendants, the
Daily Star reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The court referred the case of another defendant to a special
court for juvenile delinquents because he is under 18 years
old. The court acquitted four others because they are over 60
years old. (BC-Lebanon-Militiamen-Sentenced)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISTANBUL -- The death toll has risen above the 10,000 mark in
the powerful earthquake which hit northwest Turkey early Tuesday
morning, Turkish television reported Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
According to the NTV, a popular private news channel covering
the event 24 hours a day, 10,059 people had been confirmed dead
and more than 45,000 were injured.
</P>
<P>
And 35,000 people were still believed trapped under the rubble.
</P>
<P>
Since the quake, measuring 7.4-degrees on the Richter scale,
struck Turkey at 3:02 a.m. (0002 GMT) Tuesday, 56 aftershocks
with magnitude over four degrees have been recorded.
(BC-Turkey-Quake Toll)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISTANBUL -- A Turkish plane crashed into the Marmara Sea near
western Turkey Friday afternoon, a Turkish television reported
here.
</P>
<P>
The private news channel NTV said one of the three people on
board was rescued from the sea, and the search for the other two
was underway.
</P>
<P>
No other details of the crash were available so far, and
the place of departure as well as the destination of the
plane were unclear. (BC-Turkey-Plane-Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran on Friday rejected U.S. media accusations that
its armed forces are producing unconventional weapons.
</P>
<P>
According to the Islamic Republic News Agency, the Defense
Ministry said in a press release that U.S. newspapers violated
their professional principles in making this claim.
</P>
<P>
U.S. newspapers did so "under the influence of extreme
political leanings, to their own discredit," said the release.
</P>
<P>
Iran had been the number one victim of chemical and biological
weapons, and has consistently led and supported international
campaigns for destruction of all unconventional weapons, it said.
(BC-Iran-US-Denial)

20/08/99 19:52 GMT

NNNN
04:03 04:03 g # PAB
</P>
</TEXT>
