<HEADLINE> Ethiopians Urged to Overcome Food Shortage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Agriculture
Ministry Friday called on people of the whole country to exert
efforts to tackle the problems of food shortage and drought.
</P>
<P>
Acting Agriculture Minister Mengistu Huluka said at a panel
that the government are making efforts to attain the goal of food
self-sufficiency through the application of improved agricultural
technology and inputs.
</P>
<P>
He noted that expanding small-scale irrigation projects in
those places affected by recurrent drought is one of the solutions
to solve food shortage problem.
</P>
<P>
According to Mengistu, more than two million hectares of hilly
and mountainous areas in Ethiopia has so far not been cultivated
while 14 million hectares of land has been heavily eroded.
</P>
<P>
Besides, he said, there is also 27 million hectares of other
land that has been denuded.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia, with a population of 60 million, is an
agriculture-dominated country, which has long been striving for
food self-sufficiency.
</P>
<P>
The Horn of Africa country, depending on natural harvest,
suffered a lot from food crisis this year following months of
drought in many parts of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
