<HEADLINE> Annan Calls for More Relief Aid to Quake-Stricken </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 20 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan on Friday urged governments and voluntary agencies to
redouble their efforts to help meet Turkey's earthquake relief
needs in the weeks and months ahead.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued through his spokesman, Annan said: "We
are all aware of the magnitude of the devastation and suffering
caused by this tragedy. The needs remain enormous, both for
initial relief and rehabilitation."
</P>
<P>
The United Nations itself is providing all possible assistance
and is prepared to offer its services to coordinate the broader
international effort, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The quake measuring 7.4 on the Richter scale rocked Istanbul
Tuesday morning with more than 10,000 deaths already confirmed and
over 45,000 injuries. Some 35,000 people were still believed
trapped under the rubble. 
</P>
</TEXT>
