<HEADLINE> Aircraft for Savimbi Detained in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- An aircraft rushing supplies for
Angola's rebel militiamen has been detained in Zambia, official
radio station reported here Friday.
</P>
<P>
National Radio of Angola (RNA) said that the plane from Bangui,
capital of the Central African Republic, flew to Zambia in a bid
to carry fuel to Angola's rebel National Union for Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA), which controlled Angola's area
bordering Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft of the "Meridiem Aire Nairobi" started from
Bangui, the so- called "trading post of provisions for UNITA, flew
to the rebel's diamond producing area in Angola for UNITA, said
RNA.
</P>
<P>
No more details were revealed.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government has been accusing some African countries
of supplying the UNITA, including its neighbor Zambia, with
materials including arms, according to RNA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
