<HEADLINE> Afghan Factions Held Responsible for Child Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations on
Friday called on all warring factions in Afghanistan to refrain
from recruiting young students for war as such evidence has
already been gathered.
</P>
<P>
Youths including those aged fourteen have been found to be sent
to fight as soldiers from refugee camps in Pakistan, U.N. sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban movement has in the past two weeks recruited some
2,000 to 2,500 students in expectation of a new offensive, said
United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) Representative in
Islamabad, who termed 18 as the minimum age of recruitment into
the military. 
</P>
</TEXT>
