<HEADLINE> Iran Denies Production of Unconventional Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Friday rejected
U.S. media accusations that its armed forces are producing
unconventional weapons.
</P>
<P>
According to the Islamic Republic News Agency, the Defense
Ministry said in a press release that U.S. newspapers violated
their professional principles in making this claim.
</P>
<P>
U.S. newspapers did so "under the influence of extreme
political leanings, to their own discredit," said the release.
</P>
<P>
Iran had been the number one victim of chemical and biological
weapons, and has consistently led and supported international
campaigns for destruction of all unconventional weapons, it said.
</P>
<P>
Iran lost many lives in unconventional warfare during the
eight-year-long Iran-Iraq War in the 1980s. But the U.S. and its
Western allies have been accusing it of pursuing nuclear and
chemical weapons.
</P>
<P>
The press release said Iran is committed to international
conventions and its activities in those areas have been
"frequently inspected by responsible international bodies."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it said Israel has consistently denied
international inspection bodies access to its chemical and
nuclear arsenals, and has recently reached a military agreement
with Washington on the purchase of warplanes.
</P>
<P>
This is "a glaring example of U.S. support for rogue
states in the world," the Defense Ministry blasted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
