in 1994, 1996 and 1998, served and received well in the next two
sets to win the match.
</P>
<P>
Bernardo Rezende, head coach of the Brazil team, said his
players displayed good defense to win their second straight match
against Italy, which turned out to be a tough opponent because of
their aggressiveness.
</P>
<P>
Italian coach Angiolino Frigoni noted that his players
performed well and was satisfied with the result because the
scores were close.
</P>
<P>
Ana Moser led Brazil with 23 points, the same output of Italian
Vania Beccaria.
</P>
<P>
Other Brazilians who turned in double-digit scores were
Walewska Oliveira with 17 points followed by Janina Conceicao and
Virna Dias with 13 points each.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the evening, Cuba defeated South Korea 3-0 in the
opening game of the GP's Manila leg.
</P>
<P>
The four teams are actually going for crucial points that will
get them entry into the crossover semifinals where a 370,000-
dollar pot topped by a 200,000-dollar champion's prize is on offer.
</P>
<P>
Competing in the other group in Chinese Taipei are Russia,
Japan, China and the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The GP finals will be staged in Yunnan province, China on
August 28-29. 
