<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Firm Bars Illegal Use of Stolen Mobile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 20 (Xinhua) -- A leading Tanzanian mobile
phone company has taken measures to make it impossible for people
to reuse handsets acquired from the hands of thieves.
</P>
<P>
The General Manager of Mobitel, based in Dar es Salaam, Jim
Bell, said here Friday that his firm would immediately bar the
Electronic Serial Number (ESN) of a stolen handset so that any
other persons can no longer use it.
</P>
<P>
He called upon Mobitel customers to report to the Mobitel
office immediately once they lose their phones so as to start the
process of recovery.
</P>
<P>
When someone goes to a Mobitel office seeking for connection of
a used phone, Bell said, he is supposed to supply with details
about how and when he acquired the handset.
</P>
<P>
!0Many people disappeared and left the handsets in our hands for
fear of legal action, because the next step is to call the police
and arrest them, Bell said. 
