<HEADLINE> Xie Beats Galliamova in Round 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, China, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Xie Jun beat
Alisa Galliamova of Russia at the 14th round of the world women's
chess championship here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It took Xie over six hours to outwit Galliamova after 79 moves.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese now leads 8-6 over Galliamova.
</P>
<P>
As is regulated by the FIDE, the chess world ruling body,
either player who first collected 8.5 points will be the winner
and the play-off is needed if both sides tie 8-all. 
</P>
