<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT August 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU -- The youngest of the world's first giant panda
triplets died Saturday morning here at the Chengdu Giant Panda
Breeding Research Center in southwest China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
According to Professor Zhang Hemin, a giant panda specialist,
at around two o'clock this morning, a worker who was on round-the-
clock care duty found that one cub had been deserted by mother,
and the cub, who weighed 137 grams at birth, was already dead.
</P>
<P>
A medical examination showed that three-day-old little cub died
of a fatal bladder disorder, said Professor Zhang. (China-Sichuan-
Panda Cub Death)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Thirty-five people, including the bridegroom, were
killed and 11 others injured when a wall collapsed in a wedding
ceremony in Shanjan, a village in Iran's northwestern province of
East Azarbaijan.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) reported on Saturday
that the accident took place Thursday night due to the pressure
caused by a crowd of people who had gathered behind a newly
constructed site for the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Four children under the age of 10 were among the victims. The
other people killed were all men, it added. (Iran-Wedding Accident)
