<HEADLINE> Today's Diplomatic News Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights of
the diplomatic news released by Xinhua today:
</P>
<P>
UNICEF Exhibition Opens in Beijing
</P>
<P>
A four-day UNICEF exhibition opened here today to illustrate
cooperation projects with China and the joint effort to improve
living conditions for women and children.
</P>
<P>
Edwin J.Judd, UNICEF representative in China, said today that
the exhibition is also intended to celebrate the 50th anniversary
of the People's Republic of China and UNICEF's 20 years in China.
</P>
<P>
UNICEF established its China office in 1979 and since then it
has expanded cooperation with organizations like the Health,
Education, and Civil Affairs ministries and the All-China Women's
Federation and non-governmental organizations to provide community-
based services like basic medical and health care, nutrition
information, primary education, and sanitary drinking water.
</P>
<P>
 NPC Vice-Chairman Meets Japanese Visitors
</P>
<P>
Jiang Chunyun, vice-chairman of China's National People's
Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met here today with a
delegation from the Japan-China Lawyers Exchange Association.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese delegation, headed by Hayama Mizuki, vice-
president of the association, is visiting China at the invitation
of the Commission of Legislative Affairs of the NPC Standing
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Int'l Children's Choir Festival Begins
</P>
<P>
Children's choruses from 12 countries and regions staged a
concert here tonight, marking the beginning of the International
Children's Choir Festival-Beijing 1999.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing attended the opening ceremony
together with about 700 teenage singers from 14 choruses of many
countries and regions as well as a special chorus composed of
children from all five continents.
</P>
<P>
During the six-day festival, the choruses will put on six
performances in Beijing and Tianjin, the largest port city in
north China. 
</P>
