<BODY>
<HEADLINE> '99 Int'l Education Exposition Closes in Changchun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- '99 International Education
Exposition closed here today in Changchun, capital of northeast
China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
Some 150,000 people visited the four-day exposition which
gathered 380 colleges and universities, educational institutions,
and teaching materials manufacturers from 23 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The exposition covered all aspects of education, from the joint
administration of schools and exchange-student programs for
universities to the application of new teaching materials and
exhibitions of current education publications.
</P>
<P>
Agreements were signed on 124 cooperation programs for
administration and exchanges of students and faculties and
establishing sisterships between Chinese and foreign universities.
</P>
<P>
The exposition also displayed over 3,000 kinds of educational
materials, resulting in a 12 million yuan worth of business
contracts.
</P>
<P>
An international education forum was also held during the four-
day event, where participating universities and colleges discussed
higher learning in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, the Changchun municipal
government plans to hold another education exposition next year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
