<HEADLINE> 35 People Killed in Wall Collapses in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-five people, including
the bridegroom, were killed and 11 others injured when a
wall collapsed in a wedding ceremony in Shanjan, a village
in Iran's northwestern province of East Azarbaijan.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) reported on Saturday
that the accident took place Thursday night due to the pressure
caused by a crowd of people who had gathered behind a newly
constructed site for the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Four children under the age of 10 were among the victims. The
other people killed were all men, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
