<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Int'l Children's Choir Festival Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Children's choruses from 12
countries and regions staged a concert here tonight, marking the
beginning of the International Children's Choir Festival-Beijing
1999.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing attended the opening ceremony
together with about 700 teenage singers from 14 choruses of many
countries and regions as well as a special chorus composed of
children from all five continents.
</P>
<P>
During the six-day festival, the choruses will put on six
performances in Beijing and Tianjin, the largest port city in
north China.
</P>
<P>
With peace, friendship, and progress as its theme, the festival
is sponsored by the Chinese People's Association for Friendship
with Foreign Countries, the International Society for Children's
Choral &AMP; Performing Arts (ISCCPA), and Lucent Technologies (China)
Co., Ltd..
</P>
<P>
ISCCPA is an international organization with some 20 member
countries, and it has organized five such festivals in Hong Kong
and the United States since 1978. 
</P>
</TEXT>
