<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Channels More Funds to Promote Volunteerism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region government has approved more than five
million HK dollars this year to subsidize projects promoting
volunteerism among young people.
</P>
<P>
Funds have been channeled to support 127 projects under the
second phase of the Youth Community Service Funding Scheme,
according to a spokesman for the Commission on Youth.
</P>
<P>
"The projects will provide some 120,000 participation times for
young volunteers aged between 15 and 24 to take part in a wide
range of meaningful community service activities," the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
These include services for the elderly, tutoring students,
recreational and cultural activities, visits and exhibitions, he
added.
</P>
<P>
More than five million HK dollars have been approved on these
projects which will be completed towards the end of this year, the
spokesman said, adding that about 110 community services projects
sponsored under the first phase of the project have been completed
around June this year.
</P>
<P>
"The participants have also benefited by learning how to work
with others, acquiring leadership skills, and being better
equipped to cope with success and failure in the future," the
spokesman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
