<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Customs Cracks down on Pirated Discs, Fake Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Customs, in a joint
operation with local police, Saturday arrested 10 men and seized
more than 37,000 pirated or obscene optical discs.
</P>
<P>
Of the seized discs, about 22,000 are obscene video compact
discs, with an estimated market value of 448,000 HK dollars. There
are also some 14,900 pirated VCDs with an estimated value of 245,
000 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Customs officers of the Intellectual Property Investigation
Bureau also seized 655,000 HK dollars worth of counterfeit goods
in a three-day operation, according to a spokesman for the Customs
and Excise Department.
</P>
<P>
In the past seven months, customs officers have seized 19
million units of counterfeit goods worth a total of 45 million HK
dollars (5.76 million U.S. dollars), and arrested 464 suspects.
</P>
<P>
"We shall continue to demonstrate our determination through
this kind of operation to eradicate counterfeiting activities in
Hong Kong, to protect the rights of trade mark owners and preserve
the good image of the Hong Kong special Administrative Region,"
the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
