<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Brazil Beats South Korea in Women Volleyball GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Brazil rallied
past South Korea Saturday evening 3-2 to notch its second straight
win in the Manila leg of the World Women's Volleyball Grand Prix
1999.
</P>
<P>
The scores were 25-27, 25-20, 25-20, 19-25, 15-7. It was also
Brazil team's fifth win in the preliminary rounds of this year's
Grand Prix.
</P>
<P>
Both teams played well this evening but the Brazilians won the
fifth set behind the brilliant performances of Virna Dias, Karin
Rodrigues and Raquel Silva.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian coach Bernardo Rezende said it was difficult to beat
the South Koreans because they have the attitude of fighting until
the end.
</P>
<P>
Down 25-27 in the first set, the Brazilians came back strong in
the next two frames but went down again in the third set with 19-
25.
</P>
<P>
Rezende, however, said his team was confident of winning the
match after taking a 10-4 lead in the final round of the match.
</P>
<P>
South Korea tried to come back but lost steam down the stretch.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans banked on the powerful attacks of Chang Yoon-
Hee and Park Soo-Jeong to win the first and fourth sets.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the evening, Cuba defeated Italy 3-1 in the third
match of the Manila leg.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Cuba beat South Korea with with 3-0 while Brazil
defeated Italy with 3-1.
</P>
<P>
The four teams will compete each other on Sunday afternoon with
Italy vs. South Korea and Cuba vs. Brazil.
</P>
<P>
They are actually going for crucial points that will get them
entry into the crossover semifinals where a 370,000-dollar pot
topped by a 200,000-dollar champion's prize is on offer.
</P>
<P>
Competing in the other group in Chinese Tapei are Russia, Japan,
China and the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The GP finals will be staged in Yunnan province, China on
August 28-29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
