<HEADLINE> Rare Coin Auction to Be Held in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 21 (Xinhua) -- More than 600 rare and precious
coins will be auctioned off at a function scheduled to be held
here on September 11.
</P>
<P>
The coins range from the Qin Dynasty (221 B.C.-207 B.C.) to the
modern era and are made of a variety of materials including gold,
silver, copper, nickel, paper, cloth, and ceramics, according to
Fan Ganping, deputy president of the Shanghai International
Commodities Auction Co. Ltd., the auction's organizer.
</P>
<P>
"China has a long history of producing coins, which are
considered the epitome of the country's social and economic
development at any given period of time," said Fan.
</P>
<P>
The hobby to collecting coins has gradually become a new trend
in China because people believe that coins have a stable
investment value.
</P>
<P>
Fan said an exhibition of the coins will also be held from
September 8-10, prior to the auction.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, another auction of over 400 art works,
including 200 pieces of painting and calligraphy and some 100
items of ceramics and jade was held today in Hohhot, capital of
north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
