<HEADLINE> Gesang Namje Wins Horse Race in Ethnic Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Gesang Namje burst into tears
after he claimed the gold medal in horse race of the sixth
national ethnic games on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Gesang, a former serf, didn't race for himself until the year
of 1959 when the Democratic Reform was launched in Tibet,
abolishing the system of exploitation and separating religion from
government.
</P>
<P>
Standing on the prize platform, Gesang showed a V sign as the
drizzles mixed with the tears on his weather-beaten face.
</P>
<P>
The 60-year-old racer, who earlier came in sixth both in the 1,
000m and 2,000m horse walk competition, lived up to expectation to
win the 3,000m race on Saturday. 
