<HEADLINE> World Philately Exhibition Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The ten-day China 1999 World
Philately Exhibition opened today in Beijing's International
Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition covers 42,000 sq.m of space and includes a total
of 3,322 frames of stamps and three display cases of stamps from
private collections and museums, including the world's first stamp.
</P>
<P>
Postal administrations from 39 countries, and stamp collectors
from 16 countries and regions are participating in the general
exhibit, and philatelists from 67 countries and regions will take
part in a stamp competition during the event.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jichuan, Minister of Information Industry, said at today's
opening ceremony that stamp collecting has become the most popular
activity in the world because it promotes cultural exchanges among
nations.
</P>
<P>
He said that this exhibition will help promote the rapid and
healthy development of philately in China and the world, while
providing a venue for cooperation and exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Activities during the exhibition will also include a gathering
of young stamp collectors and several seminars, along with the
stamp show.
</P>
<P>
China now has some 20 million stamp collectors across the
country, the largest contingent of stamp-fanciers in the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
