<HEADLINE> British Warship to Visit Kuwait Wednesday: Embassy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 21 (Xinhua) -- British warship HMS
Birmingham will arrive here Wednesday on her second visit to
Kuwait since last June, the British Embassy said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
HMS Birmingham, which is the third generation since the first
Birmingham was built in 1914, is a Type 42 destroyer, and is
capable of dealing with both surface and underwater targets, the
Embassy said in a statement quoted by Kuwait News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the ship, which is mainly an air defense
ship, is equipped with Sea Dart missile system with a range of
about 30 miles (48 kilometers).
</P>
<P>
It is also equipped with an automatic 4.5" KM 8 Gun and the
Phalanz radar guided battling gun. The automatic 4.5" KM 8 Gun was
effectively used against aircraft and surface ships during the
Falklands conflict between Britain and Argentina in 1982.
</P>
<P>
HMS Birmingham, with an overall length of 412 feet and a
discharge capacity of 4,000 tons, carries on board Lynx ASW
helicopter, which can carry Sea Skua missiles.
</P>
<P>
The British ship called on Kuwait last June, when a series of
lectures and discussions were held on board. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
