<HEADLINE> Cuba Beats Italy in Women Volleyball GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- World champion Cuba defeated
Italy 3-1 on Saturday afternoon in the Manila leg of the World
Women's Volleyball Grand Prix.
</P>
<P>
It is the second victory the Cubans scored in the preliminary
rounds of the Grand Prix. Their winning scores were 25-21, 22-25,
25-23, 27-25.
</P>
<P>
Cuba worked very hard to win the match in nearly two hours
because the Italians played aggressively throughout the game.
</P>
<P>
On Friday evening, Cuba smashed South Korea 3-0 in the opener
of the Manila leg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
