<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba Gets Second Victory in Women Volleyball GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Cuba rolled to its second
straight win at the expense of Italy on Saturday afternoon in the
Manila leg of the World Women's Volleyball Grand Prix.
</P>
<P>
The scores were 25-21, 22-25, 25-23 and 27-25.
</P>
<P>
The Cubans showed its championship experience, especially in
the fourth set where they put up a solid defense to prevail.
</P>
<P>
The Italians also showed some class when they won the second
set and threatened the Cubans throughout the last two sets.
</P>
<P>
Cuban coach Antonio Perdomo said his team played more
cohesively compared to their match against the South Koreans on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Perdomo added that he was not concerned about how close the
match turned out but on what kind of match the Filipino audience
saw.
</P>
<P>
Ana Valle Fernandez turned in 17 points for Cuba while Taismary
Aguero and Yumilka Ruiz contributed 15 and 14 points, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Despite the loss, Italian coach Angiolino Frigoni said he was
happy that his team played very well against a very good team like
Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Vania Beccaria led Italy with 21 points followed by Simona
Rinieri with 15 and Francesca Piccinini, 14
</P>
<P>
On Friday evening, Cuba smashed South Korea 3-0 while Italy was
beaten by Brazil 1-3.
</P>
<P>
The four teams are actually going for crucial points that will
get them entry into the crossover semifinals where a 370,000-
dollar pot topped by a 200,000-dollar champion's prize is on offer.
</P>
<P>
Competing in the other group in Chinese Taipei are Russia,
Japan, China and the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The GP finals will be staged in Yunnan province, China on
August 28-29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
