a one-day meeting on security problems in the region.
</P>
<P>
Judicial and Political Affairs Counselor to the Central
American Integration System, Mauricio Herdocia, told Xinhua that
the center theme of the meeting is the Basic Treaty of Democratic
Security. (CAmerica-Security)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Mexican authorities Friday closed 18 ports along
the Gulf of Mexico to small and medium craft navigation as the
tropical storm "Bret" could strengthen into a hurricane and hit
the country's eastern coasts.
</P>
<P>
Storm Bret, carrying sustained winds at 102 kilometers per hour,
continues moving to the north of the Gulf, according to a
communique of the Communications and Transports Ministry (SCT). (
Mexico-Gulf-Storm)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PYONGYANG -- The Japan-U.S. deal on an anti-missile system,
known as the Theater Missile Defense (TMD), undermines peace and
stability in the Asia-Pacific region, said the official Korean
Central News Agency (KCNA) of the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea (DPRK).
</P>
<P>
"Such grave developments disturbing peace and stability in the
Asia-Pacific region are arousing deep apprehension and high
vigilance from among the regional people," the KCNA said in a
comment issued on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese cabinet approved the TMD plan on August 13 and
signed a formal agreement and memorandum of understanding with the
United States on Monday to jointly research the anti-ballistic
missile system. (DPRK-Japan-US)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISTANBUL -- Turkish monster earthquake measuring 7.4 on the
Richter scale has caused about 20 billion U.S. dollars in economic
loss, accounting for half of the country's budget in 1999, Turkish
experts has said here.
</P>
<P>
Local private NTV Saturday quoted the experts as saying that
the economic loss caused by the killer earthquake also accounts
for half of Turkey's domestic debt of 40 billion dollars. (Turkey-
Economic Loss)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- A Pakistani negotiating team left here Saturday
for Kandahar, headquarters of the Afghan Taliban, for talks with
Taliban leaders.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, shuttling between the Taliban and the
opposition alliance for peaceful settlement of the Afghan crisis,
is to hold talks with Taliban supreme leader Mulla Mohammad Omar,
official sources said. (Pakistan-Afghanistan-Taliban) 
</P>
