<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Set Up Special Fund for Ex-servicemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will set up a
special fund to help retired servicemen adjust to civilian life,
according to Deputy Defense Minister Abdullah Fadzil Che Wan
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The government allocates 26 million ringgit (6.842 million U.S.
dollars) a year to the Ex-Servicemen Affairs Corporation, but this
is insufficient to meet the housing, business and welfare needs of
its members, he said in Koka Baharu, some 470 kilometers north
from here, Bernama news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The deputy minister said discussions would be held with private
companies and agencies related to the defense ministry to seek
financial resources for establishing the fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
