<DOCNO> XIE19990821.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Writes Off Nigeria's Debts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Canada's High Commissioner to
Nigeria Ian Ferguson disclosed Friday that his country has
canceled all the debts Nigeria owed it, reported the Guardian, a
leading Nigerian Newspaper, Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Canada forgave all Nigeria's debts in the 1980s and we're in
the forefront of efforts in the G-7 to get some debt relief.
Nigeria is now debt free to Canada," he said in Lagos.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Canada will support the country in meeting the
recommendations of the International Monetary Fund (IMF) in the
areas of debt management and its economy so that Nigeria can go
to the Paris Club and negotiate for debt rescheduling, Ferguson
assured.
</P>
<P>
The envoy said that a joint team of Canadian International
Development Agency (CIDA) and International Development Research
Center (IDRC) would soon arrive the country to discuss ways of
developing the economy and entrenching democratic transition,
human rights, rule of law, women's equality and free media.
</P>
<P>
The proposed visit would be the first by Canadian officials in
many years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
