<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: "863 Program" Promotes Development of High Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- China began to launch the first
high technology research development plan, the "863 Program", in
February 1987. The program mainly involves science and technology
related to the development of the national economy and overall
national strength.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government decided to spend more than ten billion
yuan (about 1.2 billion US dollars) on the program before the year
2000 which focuses on projects of biological, space, information,
laser, automation, energy, new material technology and marine
techniques.
</P>
<P>
In the past 12 years since the implementation of the project,
China has made major achievements in some key technologic fields
such as two line hybrid rice, transgenic animals and plants,
genetic engineering drugs and plants' genome pattern. These
scientific findings have promoted biological development in China.
</P>
<P>
In the field of information technology, China developed large
scale parallel computing, and new era computers with its own
intellectual property rights, and have made major developments in
optical and electronic components and parts and other relevant
fields.
</P>
<P>
The "863 Program" has helped China make breakthroughs in the
field of automation. The successful ocean tests of the 6,000-meter
autonomous underwater vehicle has shown that China has acquired
the ability to conduct deep-ocean exploration.
</P>
<P>
In the field of nuclear technology, Chinese scientists have
developed high-temperature gas-cooled reactors and other kinds of
advanced reactors.
</P>
<P>
New materials such as high-performance ceramics and resin and
compound materials have also been developed with the support of
the "863 Program". 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
