<HEADLINE> Costa Rica Hit by Strong Earthquake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica was hit by an
earthquake measuring 6.7 on the open-ended Richter scale early on
Friday, the U.S. Geological Survey said.
</P>
<P>
The quake struck at 4:02 a.m. local time (1002 GMT) with its
epicenter 88 kilometers south of the capital, San Jose, said a
spokeswoman for the agency, based in Golden, Colorado.
</P>
<P>
