<HEADLINE> 111 People Feared Dead in Road Accident in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- At least 111 people were feared
dead when two buses fell into a roadside ditch on Dhaka-Sylhet
Highway in northeastern Bangladesh's Narsingdi district Friday
night, press reports said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Police said a Dhaka-bound bus from Bhairab, Kishoreganj
district, 292 kilometers northeast of here, and a bus from Dhaka
heading for Habiganj, also in the northeast, fell into the ditch
with about three meter deep water at about 8:30 p.m. local time.
</P>
<P>
Local people rushed to the spot and launched a rescue
operation, and the police joined them after hearing the news.
</P>
<P>
The buses were carrying 120 passengers, but only nine people
were rescued immediately after the accident.
</P>
<P>
"Many people, mostly women and children, might have met with
the tragic end of their lives as both the buses plunged into deep
water," local people were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The rescued nine were admitted to Narsingdi Sadar Hospital, and
the rescue operation was continuing.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident was unknown. 
</P>
