<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Crude Basket Price Surges to 18.2 Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan basket of crude
oil prices rose by 37 U.S. cents this week to 18.20 dollars per
barrel thanks to an increase in oil demand, the Ministry of Energy
and Mines said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Oil prices have increased over six dollars since March this
year, due to a daily production cut of 2 million barrels by oil
producing countries. They have witnessed a rebound of 89 percent
since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Venezuela's state oil company Petroleos de Venezuela
registered an 84 percent loss in profits during the petroleum
market crisis.
</P>
<P>
Basket of crude oil prices in 1998 slipped by 5.75 dollars, or
43.5 percent per barrel, resulting in a 6-billion-dollar loss in
Venezuelan government revenues.
</P>
<P>
The average price in 1998 was only 10.57 dollars against 16.32
dollars in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
