<HEADLINE> China, South Korea Expected in Indonesian Open Until 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The committee of the Indonesian
Open 1999 has given the Chinese and South Korean contingents a
chance until August 23 to make up their minds about their
participation in the badminton tournament, the Antara News Agency
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
This was stated by Indonesian Open Regional Committee Chairman
Gusti Gede Agung Mega, who is also chairman of the Indonesian
Badminton Association (PBSI) Bali chapter in the provincial
capital of Denpasar on Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest information from the South Korean and
Chinese badminton committees on Friday, they were still undecided
about their participation in the tournament which will be held in
Denpasar on September 1-5.
</P>
<P>
Although China and South Korea have not made up their mind
until Friday, he believed that the two countries, considered to be
barometers of badminton in the world, would take part in the event.
</P>
<P>
Seven days to the run-up of the Indonesian Open, 13 countries
have confirmed their participation. They are Denmark, Sweden,
Malaysia, Thailand, the Netherlands, Finland, Italy, Singapore,
Brunei, Japan, Belgium, Germany and host Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Denmark will field a full team in the 150,000 U.S. dollars four-
star tournament. Among its players are the 1999 All-England
champion Peter Gade Christensen, the 1996 Olympic gold medalist
Poul-Erik Hoyer-Larsen and the 1999 World Champion Camilla Martin.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia will also send a full team of, among others, Wong
Choon Han, Roslin Hashim and Rashid Sidek while Sweden will also
send a full team, including Tomas Johansson and Daniel Eriksson in
the singles and Par-Gunnar Jonsson and Peter Axelsson in the
doubles.
</P>
<P>
Host Indonesia will field a full team comprising, among others,
Hendrawan, Budi Santoso, Taufik Hidayat, Cindana Hartono, men's
doubles of Candra Wijaya and Tony Gunawan, Ricky Subagja and Rexy
Mainaky.
</P>
<P>
After the championships, Indonesia and Malaysia will field some
of their players for a duel meet in Yogyakarta on September 7.
</P>
