<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Exports Shrink </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan traditional exports
will shrink 30 percent by the end of the year, compared to 1998,
President of the Venezuelan Exporters Association (AVEX) Luisa
Romero said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Non-traditional exports, excluding oil and steel, will drop
from 4.7 billion dollars in 1998 to 3.4 billion dollars in 1999,
said Romero.
</P>
<P>
These kinds of exports amounted to 2.6 billion dollars between
January and June, and have dwindled about 26 percent, said Romero.
</P>
<P>
The official attributed the drop in exports to a reduction in
imports by Venezuela's regional partners who are also suffering
from an economic contraction and an avalanche of surplus Asian
commodities. 
</P>
