<HEADLINE> New Subway in Beijing To Go Into Test Running </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The new subway section from
Fuxingmen to Bawangfen will go into test operation on September 28,
said Gao Shucai, an official in charge of municipal subway
administration.
</P>
<P>
The section, with a total length of 13.5 km, is an artery line
running under the Chang'an Avenue, with 12 stations along the way.
</P>
<P>
Gao said that the section for test on the day is from the
western Tian'anmen Square to Bawangfen, totaling 10.7 km, and the
train interval will be ten minutes. The operating time is 06:30 to
21:30, with 54 trains putting into use.
</P>
<P>
And it will be operating separately from the other parts of the
underground railway, which means people will have to buy another
ticket of 2 yuan to go along the newly-built section. The test
period will last till June, 2000.
</P>
<P>
The total length of the city's operational subway will then be
55 km. 
</P>
