<HEADLINE> Ancient City Wall in North China Under Restoration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- An ancient city wall in Taiyuan,
the capital of North China's Hebei Province, has been undergoing
restoration and is expected to be reopened to the public by
October next year.
</P>
<P>
The ancient wall was built during the Ming Dynasty (1368-1644)
and is over 600 years old.
</P>
<P>
The restoration project was started by removing the buildings
near the wall, and then cementing and expanding it to a length of
280 meters and a height of 11.38 meters. When the restoration is
completed, there will also be a three-story tower rising above the
city gate. 
</P>
