<HEADLINE> Earthquake Topples 3 Houses in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 20 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 6.5
on the Richter scale shook western Panama on Friday, partially
destroying three houses in the rural community of La Mesa, some
250 kilometers west of the capital.
</P>
<P>
Jorge Correa, Director of the National Civil Protection System,
said the quake was more intense in the provinces of Bocas del Toro,
Chiriqui (both bordering Costa Rica, where the epicenter was
located), Veraguas and Herrera, but no deaths or injuries were
reported in that area.
</P>
<P>
Local adobe houses showed cracks in their walls and structures.
</P>
<P>
The University of Panama Institute of Geosciences announced
that the quake occurred at 05:02 local time (10:02 GMT), with its
epicenter 30 kilometers south of the southern city of Quepos in
Costa Rica. 
