<HEADLINE> UPU Post Office Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A special post office in
Beijing to serve delegates to the 22nd Congress of the Universal
Postal Union (UPU) has already been into operation since yesterday,
said the congress organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
The post office, located in the meeting place, the
International Conference Center, will handle international and
domestic mails, newspapers and postal stamps, provide postal check
and consultation, as well as fax service during the 22nd Congress
from August 23 to September 15.
</P>
<P>
The post office is expected to receive around 70 tons of mails
into China, and send 800 to 1,000 tons out of China, and to offer
services to some 20,000 people, according to the organizing
committee.
</P>
<P>
The UPU was founded in 1874 and became a special body of the
United Nations responsible for postal affairs in 1948. The
Congress, the supreme decision making body, generally meets every
five years. And the headquarters of the UPU International Bureau
is in Bern, Switzerland, its current Director-General being Thomas
Leavey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
