</P>
<P>
BONN -- Amid a drastic decline of electricity price caused by
the bitter competition among domestic power providers,
spokespersons of Germany's ruling Social Democratic Party (SPD) on
Friday urged the federal authorities to regulate the market.
</P>
<P>
The continuously dropping power price, they said, would hinder
the employment of environment-friendly technologies in electricity
generation, and would leave those small power plants under huge
market pressure. (Germany-Price War)
</P>
<P>
