</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- Rwanda and Tanzania will soon open up Isaka inland
dry port by September of this year in a bid to transport goods in
and out of Rwanda via Dar-es-Salaam port more easily, Rwanda News
Agency (RNA) reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The RNA quoted Vincent Biruta, Rwandan Minister of Transport
and Telecommunications, as saying that the inland port will be
opened at Isaka in northwestern Tanzania. (Rwanda-Dry Port)
</P>
<P>
