<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Hits Western, Central Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake measuring 5.5
on the open-ended Richter scale jolted western and central Japan
on Saturday morning, the meteorological agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties or damage, and no
tsunami or tidal wave warnings were issued.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake, which struck Wakayama, Mie and
Aichi prefectures at around 5:33 a.m. (local time), was estimated
to be 70 kilometers underground in the northern part of Wakayama
Prefecture, the agency said. 
