<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Is to Export 4 Mln Tons of Rice This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has already exported more
than 3 million tons of rice so far and will surely export at least
4 million tons of rice this year, Vietnam's business newspaper The
Saigon Times Daily reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the first 17 days of August, an official of the Vietnamese
Food Association said, Vietnam shipped some 332,000 tons of rice
abroad, bringing the total export volume this year to more than
3.1 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Export price is 3-5 U.S. dollars higher than earlier in the
month. Currently the high-grade 5 percent broken is generally
quoted at 231-232 U.S. dollars per ton FOB at Vietnam's Saigon
Port, while quotations for the low-grade 25 percent broken center
around 213 U.S. dollars per ton.
</P>
<P>
More than 132,000 tons of rice was being loaded on 16 vessels
this week in the Saigon Port, with destinations including
Indonesia, Ghana, Iraq and Tanzania. Last week 14 vessels loaded
nearly 110,000 tons of rice.
</P>
<P>
Paddy price in Mekong Delta, Vietnamese biggest rice bowl, has
also risen with the selling price of the summer-autumn paddy at
1,700-1,800 Vietnamese dong (0.12 -- 0.13 U.S. dollars) per
kilogram.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the price of high-class winter-spring paddy are
staying at 2,000 Vietnamese dong (0.14 U.S. dollars) per kilogram.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's summer-autumn paddy yield could amount to 7.3 million
tons, some 900,000 tons higher than expected, according to an
official of the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has already contracted to ship 3.7 million tons of rice
so far this year, said the official, adding that the country would
surely export at least four million tons overall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
